# SkillGod — Automatic Skill & Memory Injection

Before responding to any coding-related request, call the `sg_inject_context` MCP
tool with the user's request as the `task` argument, and use its returned context
(relevant skills + project memory) to inform your response.

After completing each response, call the `sg_capture_turn` MCP tool with:
- `task`: the user's request (verbatim or summarised)
- `output`: a concise summary of what you decided or built this turn
  (architectural choices, fixes, non-obvious decisions — not routine edits)

Project memory is also written into AGENTS.md / CLAUDE.md and per-IDE
skillgod-memory digest files — treat those as authoritative history.

Both MCP calls apply to every coding request in this project, not just some of them.
